fg_segments: Protecting your privacy is very important to us. We're telling you about our privacy policy so you know what information we collect, why we collect it, and what we do with it.
This privacy notice is for IslamicFinder.org. This site is referred to as "IslamicFinder.org" or "IF" throughout the rest of this notice and is maintained and operated by IslamicFinder.
Operating IslamicFinder.org, does not collect your name, email address, location or other similar information unless you choose to provide it.
We do collect other limited information automatically from visitors who read, browse, and/or download information from our site.
We do this so we can understand how the site is being used and how we can make it more helpful.
If you create a user account by signing up from IslamicFinder, and use our module on the site (such as PrayerBook), we save your data of prayer logging that you added from our Athan application.
We keep your data save of complete prayer logging throughout all past months and years.

This information is collected in order to give you full information about your prayers progress in statistical form i.e. offered prayers, missed prayers, most offered prayers, most missed prayer and best day throughout the month.
The important point is that IslamicFinder keeps users information confidential and does not sell any information that we got after your sign up process to any third party.
Types of information we collect Information which is automatically collected:
When you browse Certain information about your visit can be collected when you browse our website.
When you browse IslamicFinder.org, we, and in some cases our third-party service providers, can collect the following types of information about your visit, including:

IP address (an IP or internet protocol address is a number that is automatically assigned to a device connected to the web) Approximate geographic location based on the IP address of the user's local system or internet service provider.

Operating system (which is software that directs a computer's basic functions such as executing programs and managing storage) for the device that you are using and information about the browser you used when visiting the site.
Date and time of your visit. Pages you visited.
Address of the website that connected you to IslamicFinder.org (such as google.com)
Device type (desktop computer, tablet, or type of mobile device)
Screen resolution Browser language Geographic location Time spent on pages Scroll depth –
The measure of how much of a web page was viewed User events (e.g. clicking a button)
Cookies of prayer times setting i.e. Calculation method, juristic method, Latitude and Longitude of your selected location.

We use this information to measure the number of visitors to our site and its various sections, to help make our site more useful to visitors, and to improve our public education and outreach through digital advertising.
Also, this information is sometimes used to personalize the content we show to you on third-party sites.

Information which you may provide: When you request information: We collect information including your name, email address or mobile phone number to deliver Islamic newsletter and use mobile number to give you link of Athan Application on your cell number by taking your subscription consent first.
We use this information to complete the subscription process and provide you with useful information.
You can opt out of these subscriptions at any time by unsubscribe yourself from newsletter email.
Link on unsubscribe has been given in newsletter How we uses information collected on IslamicFinder.org
When calculating prayer times according to your Current location: We write multiple cookies of your browser to calculate exact prayer times according to your current location.
If you delete these cookies from your browser then we need to recalculate prayer times by using these cookies when you visit our page next time.
Following cookies are saved in your browser from our site usage:
Calculation Method (Prayer times calculation based on this cookie)
Current detected Location (To calculate exact prayer times, Calendar and Qibla direction according to users location)

Last detected location (Save users previous city location so that he can change location easily from our recent location option) dhuharTimeAfterZawal (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) ishaTimeAdjustment (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) fajarAngle
(Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) ishaAngle (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) hijriDateAdjustment (
Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) juristicMethod (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) maghribTimeAfterSunset (

Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) lastUpdatedLocation (Users last updated location saved to calculate prayer times) onBoardingDisplayed (To restrict that onboarding of site not displayed to user every time) recentLocations (To identify users recent location) timeZoneDifference (To calculate exact prayer times) translator (To show Quran translation according to users location)

When sending you IslamicFinder Emails or Messages: IF uses the email address (or mobile phone number) you provide us to send emails or Short Message Service (SMS) messages related to latest uploaded Islamic content and Athan application installation, if you have given us permission to send you such emails and text messages.
When conducting surveys and improving services: IF also uses online surveys to collect opinions and feedback.
You don't have to answer these questions. If you do answer these questions, do not include any personally identifiable information in your answers.
We analyze and use the information from these surveys to improve the site's operation and content.
The information is available only to managers, members of the communications and other designated IslamicFinder staff and contractors who require this information to perform their duties.
When using third-party tools for website analytics: IF uses a variety of third-party web tools for web analytics.
IF uses these tools to collect basic information about visits to IslamicFinder.org.

This information is then used to maintain the website including: monitoring site stability, measuring site traffic, optimizing site content, improving search engine optimization and may help make the site more useful to visitors.
The staff analyzes the data collected from these tools.
The reports are available only to managers and internal teams who implement core functionality of IslamicFinder.
When using third-party tools for outreach through digital advertising: Uses third-party web services to conduct outreach and education through the use of digital advertising from the users Locations.
These third-party services may collect information through the use of web beacons that are located on our pages.

A web beacon is a see-through graphic image (usually 1 pixel x 1 pixel) that is placed on a web page and, in combination with a cookie, allows us to collect information regarding the use of the web page that contains the web beacon.

We use web beacons to tell when a user is redirected to IslamicFinder.org because of a Locations advertisement that we ran on another website was clicked on or otherwise interacted with (known as "click tracking" or "conversion tracking") and to better target Locations advertisements (known as "retargeting"). uses third-party tools to help deliver advertising.
Vendors that operate the third-party tools may also gather information about your visits to third-party sites outside of IslamicFinder.org.

However, while does not track your individual-level activity on the Internet outside of IslamicFinder.org, our vendors may collect information automatically collected by IslamicFinder.org (not information you provide),and combine it with data they collect elsewhere for targeted advertising purposes.
You can opt out of this type of data collection via Privacy Manager, Ad Choices, and Do Not Track.
See Your Choices about tracking and data collection below for methods to opt out of this type of collection.
The outreach and education analytics tools provide reports which aggregate data such as the number of clicks on advertisements.

The reports are available only to managers, teams who implement the insurance affordability programs represented on IslamicFinder.org, members of the IslamicFinder.org communications and web team, and other designated IslamicFinder staff and contractors who need this information to perform their duties.
Cookie Policy of IslamicFinder.org This Cookie Policy was last modified on 20/05/2018.
IslamicFinder Organization ("us", "we", or "our") operates https://www.islamicfinder.org (the "Site").
The IslamicFinder website uses cookies to improve the users experience while browsing/visiting the website.
This website uses a cookie control system which enables the user to allow or disallow the use of cookies on their computer / device upon their first website visit.
This complies with recent legislation requirements for websites to attain explicit consent from their users before leaving behind or reading files such as cookies on a user's computer / device.
Cookies are small files that are saved to the user's computer's hard drive which track, save and store information about the user's interactions and usage of the website.
This allows the website to provide its users with a personalized experience.

In order for our users to disallow or discontinue the use and saving of cookies from this website on their computer's hard drive, necessary steps will have to be taken within their web browsers security settings which will block all website cookies and it's external serving vendors.
This website uses tracking software to monitor it's visitors to better understand their website usage.
This tracking software is provided by Google Analytics, which uses cookies to monitor visitor's usage.

The software will automatically save a cookie to your computer's hard drive in order to track your engagement and usage of the IslamicFinder website, but it won't collect, save or store personal information of users.
You can read Google's privacy policy for further information [http://www.google.com/privacy.html].
Other cookies might be saved to your computer's hard drive by external websites or vendors when this website uses referral programs, sponsored links or advertisements.
Such cookies are used for conversion and referral tracking, which typically expire within 30 days, though some may take longer.
No personal information is saved, collected or stored. WHICH COOKIES WE ARE USING:
When you use or access our Services, we may place several cookies files in your web browser.
We use cookies for the following purposes; to enable certain functions of our Service, to provide analytics, to store preferences and to enable advertisements.
Our site does not keep or use any personal information.
Any anonymous information is handled according to our Privacy Policy as seen on our website.
We only use cookies to get accurate prayer times according to users location and Quran settings according to user preferences. We are using following cookies:
Calculation Method (Prayer times calculation based on this cookie)
Current detected Location (To calculate exact prayer times, Calendar and Qibla direction according to users location)

Last detected location (Save users previous city location so that he can change location easily from our recent location option) dhuharTimeAfterZawal (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) ishaTimeAdjustment (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) fajarAngle
(Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) ishaAngle (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) hijriDateAdjustment (
Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) juristicMethod (Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) maghribTimeAfterSunset (

Users preference of prayer times setting saved in this cookie) lastUpdatedLocation (Users last updated location saved to calculate prayer times) onBoardingDisplayed (To restrict that onboarding of site not displayed to user every time) recentLocations (To identify users recent location) timeZoneDifference (To calculate exact prayer times) translator (To show Quran translation according to users location)
However, you may prefer to disable cookies on this site and on others.
The most effective way to do this is to disable cookies in your browser.
We suggest consulting the 'Help' section of your browser, but be aware that certain functionality may not be available to you.
THIRD-PARTY COOKIES In addition to our own cookies, we may also use various third-party cookies to report usages statistics.
This includes social media analytics, Google Analytics and third-party marketing software analytics.
This information is collected to see the success of our own advertising campaigns.
For more information on this subject, please visit www.aboutcookies.org website.

Your Choices About Tracking and Data Collection on IslamicFinder.org IslamicFinder.org offers a Privacy Manager which gives you control over what tracking and data collection takes place during your visit.
Third-party tools are enabled by default to provide a quality consumer experience.
The privacy manager provides you with the choice to opt-in or to opt-out of the different categories of third-party tools used by IslamicFinder.org: Advertising, Analytics, or Social Media.
The privacy manager prevents cookies, web beacons, and Local Storage Objects from being placed on your device.

The privacy manager also prevents third-party tools from loading regardless of your cookie settings, which provides consumers with an additional layer of privacy that prevents the tool from loading at all.

Because the privacy manager creates a cookie in your browser, the opt-in and opt-out choices you make through the privacy manager will only be effective on the device and browser you used to make your choices, and your choices will expire when the cookie expires Google AdSense Ads – includes the Ad Choices icon on all digital advertising that uses "conversion-tracking" or "re-targeting".
The Google AdSense Ads icon is usually at or near the corner of digital ads.
When you click on the Google AdSense Ads icon it will provide information on what company served the ad and information on how to opt-out.
For more information on Google AdSense Ads, please visit the Google AdSense Ads website.
Do Not Track – automatically observes the "Do Not Track" browser setting for digital advertising that uses "conversion-tracking" or "re-targeting".
If "Do Not Track" is set before a device visits IslamicFinder.org, third party conversion tracking and retargeting tools will not load on the site.
For more information on Do Not Track or information on how to set the Do Not Track setting in your browser go to the Do Not Track website.
How uses third-party tools by IslamicFinder.org Third-party Websites: Your activity on the third-party websites that IslamicFinder.org links to following third party tools:
Facebook Twitter Linkedin Whatsapp Instagram Disqus Addthis Twilio for SMS Service Zendesk
This is governed by the security and privacy policies of their respective websites.
You should review the privacy policies of all websites before using them so that you understand how your information may be used.

Website Analytics Tools: These tools collect basic site usage information such as: how many visits IslamicFinder.org receives, the pages visited by consumers, time spent on the site, the number of return visits to the site, the approximate location of the device used to access the site, types of devices used, etc.
This information is then used to maintain the website including: monitoring site stability, measuring site traffic, optimizing site content, and improving the consumer experience.
Use the IslamicFinder.org privacy manager to opt-out of website analytics tools.
HOW TO CONTACT US: If you have any questions about these Terms or the Service, please contact us via sending an email at privacy@islamicfinder.org.
Deletion of Account Upon request of user, we will delete users complete profile information from our database.
We will only keep users email address just for record purpose that will not be used for any further email notifications.
Moreover, we have option of delete account in Athan application from Edit Profile menu.
If our users sign up from our IslamicFinder website only then they can delete account from Athan Application by signing in with same email address.

When sending you IslamicFinder Emails or
						Messages:
IF uses the email address (or mobile phone

						(SMS) messages related to latest uploaded Islamic content and
						Athan application installation, if you have given us permission to
						send you such emails and text messages.
When conducting surveys and improving
						services:
IF also uses online surveys to collect
						opinions and feedback. You don’t have to answer these questions.
						If you do answer these questions, do not include any personally
						identifiable information in your answers. We analyze and use the
						information from these surveys to improve the site’s operation and
						content. The information is available only to managers, members of
						the communications and other designated IslamicFinder staff and
						contractors who require this information to perform their duties.
					
When using third-party tools for website
						analytics:
IF uses a variety of third-party web tools
						for web analytics. IF uses these tools to collect basic
						information about visits to IslamicFinder.org. This information is
						then used to maintain the website including: monitoring site
						stability, measuring site traffic, optimizing site content,
						improving search engine optimization and may help make the site
						more useful to visitors. The staff analyzes the data collected
						from these tools. The reports are available only to managers and
						internal teams who implement core functionality of IslamicFinder.
					
When using third-party tools for outreach
						through digital advertising:
Uses third-party web services to conduct
						outreach and education through the use of digital advertising from
						the users Locations. These third-party services may collect
						information through the use of web beacons that are located on our
						pages. A web beacon is a see-through graphic image (usually 1
						pixel x 1 pixel) that is placed on a web page and, in combination
						with a cookie, allows us to collect information regarding the use
						of the web page that contains the web beacon. We use web beacons
						to tell when a user is redirected to IslamicFinder.org because of
						a Locations advertisement that we ran on another website was
						clicked on or otherwise interacted with (known as “click tracking”
						or “conversion tracking”) and to better target Locations
						advertisements (known as “retargeting”). uses third-party tools to
						help deliver advertising. Vendors that operate the third-party
						tools may also gather information about your visits to third-party
						sites outside of IslamicFinder.org. However, while does not track
						your individual-level activity on the Internet outside of
						IslamicFinder.org, our vendors may collect information
						automatically collected by IslamicFinder.org (not information you
						provide),and combine it with data they collect elsewhere for
						targeted advertising purposes. You can opt out of this type of
						data collection via Privacy Manager, Ad Choices, and Do Not Track.
						See Your Choices about tracking and data collection below for
						methods to opt out of this type of collection. The outreach and
						education analytics tools provide reports which aggregate data
						such as the number of clicks on advertisements. The reports are
						available only to managers, teams who implement the insurance
						affordability programs represented on IslamicFinder.org, members
						of the IslamicFinder.org communications and web team, and other
						designated IslamicFinder staff and contractors who need this
						information to perform their duties.
Cookie Policy of IslamicFinder.org
This Cookie Policy was last modified on
						20/05/2018. IslamicFinder Organization (“us”, “we”, or “our”)
						operates https://www.islamicfinder.org (the “Site”). The
						IslamicFinder website uses cookies to improve the users experience
						while browsing/visiting the website. This website uses a cookie
						control system which enables the user to allow or disallow the use
						of cookies on their computer / device upon their first website
						visit. This complies with recent legislation requirements for
						websites to attain explicit consent from their users before
						leaving behind or reading files such as cookies on a user's
						computer / device. Cookies are small files that are saved to the
						user's computer's hard drive which track, save and store
						information about the user's interactions and usage of the
						website. This allows the website to provide its users with a
						personalized experience. In order for our users to disallow or
						discontinue the use and saving of cookies from this website on
						their computer's hard drive, necessary steps will have to be taken
						within their web browsers security settings which will block all
						website cookies and it's external serving vendors. This website
						uses tracking software to monitor it's visitors to better
						understand their website usage. This tracking software is provided
						by Google Analytics, which uses cookies to monitor visitor's
						usage. The software will automatically save a cookie to your
						computer's hard drive in order to track your engagement and usage
						of the IslamicFinder website, but it won't collect, save or store
						personal information of users. You can read Google's privacy
						policy for further information
						[http://www.google.com/privacy.html]. Other cookies might be saved
						to your computer's hard drive by external websites or vendors when
						this website uses referral programs, sponsored links or
						advertisements. Such cookies are used for conversion and referral
						tracking, which typically expire within 30 days, though some may
						take longer. No personal information is saved, collected or
						stored.
WHICH COOKIES WE ARE USING:
When you use or access our Services, we may
						place several cookies files in your web browser. We use cookies
						for the following purposes; to enable certain functions of our
						Service, to provide analytics, to store preferences and to enable
						advertisements. Our site does not keep or use any personal
						information. Any anonymous information is handled according to our

						disable cookies in your browser. We suggest consulting the ‘Help’

THIRD-PARTY COOKIES
In addition to our own cookies, we may also
						use various third-party cookies to report usages statistics. This
						includes social media analytics, Google Analytics and third-party
						marketing software analytics. This information is collected to see
						the success of our own advertising campaigns. For more information
						on this subject, please visit www.aboutcookies.org website.
Your Choices About Tracking and Data
						Collection on IslamicFinder.org
IslamicFinder.org offers a Privacy Manager
						which gives you control over what tracking and data collection
						takes place during your visit. Third-party tools are enabled by
						default to provide a quality consumer experience. The privacy
						manager provides you with the choice to opt-in or to opt-out of
						the different categories of third-party tools used by
						IslamicFinder.org: Advertising, Analytics, or Social Media. The
						privacy manager prevents cookies, web beacons, and Local Storage
						Objects from being placed on your device. The privacy manager also
						prevents third-party tools from loading regardless of your cookie
						settings, which provides consumers with an additional layer of
						privacy that prevents the tool from loading at all. Because the
						privacy manager creates a cookie in your browser, the opt-in and
						opt-out choices you make through the privacy manager will only be
						effective on the device and browser you used to make your choices,
						and your choices will expire when the cookie expires Google
						AdSense Ads – includes the Ad Choices icon on all digital
						advertising that uses “conversion-tracking” or “re-targeting”. The
						Google AdSense Ads icon is usually at or near the corner of
						digital ads. When you click on the Google AdSense Ads icon it will
						provide information on what company served the ad and information
						on how to opt-out. For more information on Google AdSense Ads,
						please visit the Google AdSense Ads website. Do Not Track –
						automatically observes the “Do Not Track” browser setting for
						digital advertising that uses “conversion-tracking” or
						“re-targeting”. If “Do Not Track” is set before a device visits
						IslamicFinder.org, third party conversion tracking and retargeting
						tools will not load on the site. For more information on Do Not
						Track or information on how to set the Do Not Track setting in
						your browser go to the Do Not Track website.

Website Analytics Tools:
These tools collect basic site usage

HOW TO CONTACT US:
If you have any questions about these Terms
						or the Service, please contact us via sending an email at

Deletion of Account
Upon request of user, we will delete users complete profile information from our database. We will only keep users email address just for record purpose that will not be used for any further email notifications. Moreover, we have option of delete account in Athan application from Edit Profile menu. If our users sign up from our IslamicFinder website only then they can delete account from Athan Application by signing in with same email address.
